The food quality at B Patisserie is so high and the experience is great. Every time I visit SF, I'll be making a trip here. FOOD Apple cinnamon almond croissant - really tasty and good Kouign Amann - flakey and soft. It's like no other I've had. SERVICE They are friendly and efficient here. There's often a long line but it moves well PARKING limited street parking.

I'm figuratively drooling even more since I've not been out to eat since March 13... but who's counting? My friend recommended this place, and I was close to missing out since baked goods don't really spark joy for me. But, we had time to kill so I stopped by for the Kouign Amman and it wow'd. Flakey outside with buttery, perfectly chewy layers inside. And the black sesame latte was uniquely delicious. This place is on my forever SF to do list.

I live upstairs and have to resist coming down. My favorites are the Pain Suisse, Chocolate Banana Almond Croissant, Kouign (all flavors are delicious), and Cinnamon Roll PRO TIP: pick up some plain croissants to-go and make breakfast sandwiches with them.

Came here around 9am on a Tuesday morning and it was pretty empty. They don't have plenty of tables and seats unfortunately so we were able to grab one of the last tables! When you walk in, it smells amazing and you see this beautiful spread of all the baked goods you could buy. There were so many options in such a large abundance it actually looks amazing. It has a nice modern and clean interior that's very welcoming and warms you up! I should have read more Yelp reviews because we didn't get the Kouign Amann which is what everybody talks about here! But what we got was so good already, that we got another pastry to-go! We had the ham and cheese croissant, the apple cinnamon oat croissant the double chocolate cookie. The ham and cheese croissant came with a large sheet of of ham on the inside and was a bit greasy but still quite savory and delicious. The apple cinnamon oat croissant was a special (they don't usually have it) and that was pretty good! Their croissants aren't super flaky and dry like other places but have a good balance of moisture and crispiness but also taste really great! We had the double chocolate cookie too! It had white chocolate chips and a chocolate dough. It was a massive cookie! Still warm, fresh and super soft - it melts in your mouth! The prices were a bit more expensive than usual, but definitely cheaper than somewhere like Tartine - but still really good. Since moving to this neighborhood I'd say that this is the new Tartine for me! I can't wait to come back, this place is fantastic!

B. Patisserie is my favorite pastries shop. It's a French bakery, that is famous for their Kouign Amann, a delicious pastries filled with crispy buttery layers, topped lightly with caramelized sugar. I would definitely recommend this place for sure. They also have other flavors, including passion fruit and chocolate, but the original is my favorite. I also enjoyed their seasonal apple almond croissants and their passion fruit bostock- if you are into something more tart and fruity. I had also ordered a hot chocolate and it was okay. We came right before it opened on a Tuesday morning and there was a already a few people waiting outside the door with us. I loved coming early to a pastry shop because of how freshly baked treats taste, and I was very surprised that it was still delicious and crispy and soft in the middle when I had them at home again that night. It's only street parking and if you are lucky and don't mind a little walk, there's a street, behind the restaurant that gives you free 2 hour parking.

We came here on a Sunday afternoon and found parking fairly easily. The bakery smells fantastic when you walk in, a mixture of warm pastries and a hint of coffee. What was purchased: + Kouign Amann - This is definitely a must get! Perfectly flakey and crispy with every bite. It gets a little messy because of the flakes but it's worth it. My sister ordered the passionfruit mango one as well but liked the original one better. + Banana Almond Croissant - This was decent, but not as flakey as the Kouign Amann. The croissant seemed a like it was left out for a while and we felt the banana flavor overpowered the almond. + Chocolate Banana Bread - Loved this, even after 3 days! It was perfectly moist with a great balance of chocolate and bananas. I was surprised that it was still so moist after two days. In the event you're not a huge chocolate fan, they do have a banana bread option which I would think would be equally delicious. + Chocolate Chip Cookie - The cookies here are fairly thin but large! I like cookies that are crispy on the outside but still chewy on the inside and this cookie was perfect. I didn't try any of the desserts that day but I would definitely go back to try those. The cakes looked fantastic as well.

This bakery came recommended to me by one of the owner's family members so of course I had to try it. Upon walking in, the smell and sight of fresh sweets, breads and chocolates engulfed all the senses making the choice between delicacies nearly impossible. I settled on a chocolate croissant and the Kouign Amann, while dad chose the banana and chocolate croissant. Each pastry was airy, delicate and flavorful. I really liked the banana croissant because it was unique and was very well executed. The banana did not overpower the chocolate and flaky pastry layers at all. The chocolate croissant was delicious not only due to the lightness of the dough and richness of the chocolate but the crunchy, sweet topping added just the right amount of texture and flavor. I enjoyed the Kouign Amann because it was so delicate yet also very clean in taste. All of the pastries and small desserts looked absolutely divine so I'm sure you will love whatever you try! Parking is a pain but there is a bus stop right in front of B Patisserie and there is always walking/biking options. The wait is not long and the line clears quickly. Ambiance is fresh and staff are very welcoming. Enjoy!

Patisserie. Did you know that, The B. in Patisserie stands for Barbara Leong, one of the founders of this awesome business, which was establish in 2011. Once we arrived I saw the line out the door and I thought the line was for the tea place next door but it was actually for B. Patisserie. The line moved pretty quick, We placed our order with one of the workers, they will either pack them for dining in or take out, once you reach the cashier line, you will pay for your items.     We came here on a Sunday afternoon and found parking fairly easily. The bakery smells fantastic when you walk in, a mixture of warm pastries and a hint of coffee.

    What was purchased:
    + Kouign Amann - This is definitely a must get! Perfectly flakey and crispy with every bite. It gets a little messy because of the flakes but it's worth it. My sister ordered the passionfruit mango one as well but liked the original one better.

    + Chocolate Banana Bread - Loved this, even after 3 days! It was perfectly moist with a great balance of chocolate and bananas. I was surprised that it was still so moist after two days.     + Chocolate Chip Cookie - The cookies here are fairly thin but large! I like cookies that are crispy on the outside but still chewy on the inside and this cookie was perfect.

    I didn't try any of the desserts that day but I would definitely go back to try those. The cakes looked fantastic as well.

    Hope to be back some day because the food was great.

    the rumors are true - B Patisserie is the best bakery you'll ever try. Yes, your bill easily can get pretty high, but it's worth it for such amazing pastries.

    The lines are usually long, so I suggest you get there as early as possible. The line goes by pretty fast though. Be prepared to know what you want though, cause they ask how many pastries you want so they can get the right box size!

    The KOUIGN AMANN is definitely what B Patisserie is known for! And you should definitely try it. It's like a caramelized croissant! VERY sweet though! I was there during their seasonal Chinese New Year menu and I highly recommend the Black Sesame Kouign Amann!

    Their banana bread is MMMMMM so good! It's ~$6-7 so it might seem pricey, but it's honestly a pretty big loaf and can last a while.

    I also got a baguette for $2.75 which is such a steal! ITS SO GOOD AND SO CHEAP! Brought it home and ate it with Brie and it was perfect.

    Another Chinese New Year menu item that I got was the Milk Tea Cake which was $7. Though pricey, this tiny cake was definitely worth it. The tea flavor just hits you mid bite and you can taste the authentic flavors. Definitely try this if you can!

    So far, I've tried:

    - Banana Chocolate Almond Croissant - My personal must-have! I think this is one of my favorite pastries of all time. There are thick chunks of chocolate and real banana throughout the inside of the croissant. It's also buttery and the textures are completely on point. Absolutely heavenly!
    - Mango Pudding - very light and refreshing, not overly sweet. Not a must-have but if you're craving this type of dessert, go for it! It tastes exactly as it looks. 5/5
    - Black Sesame Kouign Amann - I ordered this on my second visit and unfortunately, I was not the biggest fan of it. I typically like black sesame flavors but unfortunately, the flavor was too light on this one. I also felt it was too oily compared to the plain kouign amman? 2/5

    Also, did I mention that the pastries come out WARM?!

    The cafe is quite small but very cute. Tons of natural light.

    Came at around 9:40am on a Sunday, right before the rush of people. The line reached the end of the block when I left. Ordered 2 kouign amanns, a black sesame kouign amann, a mango kouign amann, a chocolate kouign amann, and a loaf of banana bread.

    Kouign Amann 5/5 stars - It was so good. The outside was crispy, and the inside was soft and buttery. Just the right amount of sugar. The pastry texture was the same for all of the kouign amanns.

    Black Sesame Kouign Amann 4.5/5 stars - I was expecting the pastry to have more of a sesame taste since it was covered in small black specks. The filling had a good sesame taste though. Sweetness was just right.

    Mango Kouign Amann 3/5 stars - My least favorite filling. The mango didn't taste natural.

    Chocolate Kouign Amann 5/5 stars - The chocolate wasn't too sweet, and it was smooth.

    Banana Bread 5/5 stars - The best banana bread I have ever had. It was so moist and flavorful and wasn't dense.

    Definitely worth the price. I didn't have to wait too long, but I would wait an hour if I had to for that banana bread.

    I made it to my 100th Review for 2019 and it's all about the Koiugn at B. Patisserie @ San Francisco!

    Oh Wow, I've always wanted to check out the original location that that created this AMAZING Kouign Amann, the ones that I've fell in love with my very first time when I tried it for the back here in Honolulu. I've been to SF a few times but didn't have a chance to stop by until my short one day visit during the first week of December. I am so happy that I can get my kouign here in Waikiki but a visit to B. Patisserie is a must to visit when in San Fran.

    When we visited, it was cold and rainy, my other half took me here upon request, after having a big breakfast I had to make a stop here no matter how full I was. We circled around and didn't have luck with street parking, although there was a parking close by, we were unsure about some of the street parking with colored ones so we just parked a street over instead of a chancing it, we fed the meter for one hour and walked over the B. Patisserie.

    Did you know that, The B. in Patisserie stands for Barbara Leong, one of the founders of this awesome business, which was establish in 2011.

    Once we arrived I saw the line out the door and I thought the line was for the tea place next door but it was actually for B. Patisserie. The line moved pretty quick, We placed our order with one of the workers, they will either pack them for dining in or take out, once you reach the  cashier line, you will pay for your items.

    My opinion, service needs improvement, this is the reason for my 4 stars. I don't remember seeing a smile from the cashier and getting any greetings of "Hi"or "Thank You". I just felt rush at the cashier but I understand, they are busy!

    Wow, it has been weeks since I last had any pastry or sweets, which is my weakness so kouign is such a treat. I was happy to see pumpkin kouign available, back home in Honolulu the pumpkin is available only during restaurant week. I got our kouign and of course coffee, and finished them off at the restaurant. There are in door and a few out door seatings, we finished off our kouign and coffee at the restaurant. I am amazed after taking a bite of my Kouign, which was super fresh, extra crispy and oh so good!! I wish I could eat more, but I had to set a limit for myself.

    After we were done, I went back in line to grab Kouign(s) for my cousin who lives in SF, they lived in SF but have never been to B. Patisserie. I also got 2 slice of the custard for our hotel sweets and that was so good too!

    Warning: When at B. Patisserie, there are TONS and TONS of pastries and desserts to choose from, it will be really hard to decide. I recommend the Kouign for first timers.

    Overall, I am so happy I got to visit the original B. Patisserie, and I cant wait to stop here again when I'm at San Fran. ((Sad face,)) I really left my heart in San Fran!!
